00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:58,785
♪

287
00:11:58,785 --> 00:11:59,819
Come on!

288
00:11:59,819 --> 00:12:01,888
Will you explain just one thing?

289
00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:03,590
Sure, what is it?

290
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:05,058
Just between you and me,

291
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,260
how bad can this
Pixie monster be?

292
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,462
I mean, with a
name like "Pixie."

293
00:12:09,462 --> 00:12:10,597
Pretty bad.

294
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:12,498
Just ask the people
in North Town.

295
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:14,400
What's happening there?

296
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:17,237
She's got a stranglehold
on the whole town.

297
00:12:17,237 --> 00:12:20,707
All the humans and monsters
are under her control.

298
00:12:20,707 --> 00:12:24,677
Word is, Moo is looking
for something really big.

299
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:26,746
And Pixie works for Moo?

300
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:29,716
I wonder what big thing
Moo is looking for.

301
00:12:29,716 --> 00:12:31,351
♪

302
00:12:31,351 --> 00:12:33,886
To have a chance,
we gotta go now.

303
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:36,289
Good luck, and take
care of yourselves.

304
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:38,224
You too, my friends.

305
00:12:38,224 --> 00:12:41,995
♪

306
00:12:41,995 --> 00:12:45,064
Captain Clay, explain to me

307
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,600
why you came
running back here.

308
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,136
Kume, I thought
that reporting to you

309
00:12:50,136 --> 00:12:53,339
was first priority,
Master Pixie.

310
00:12:53,339 --> 00:12:56,509
Explain to me why
I would want you here

311
00:12:56,509 --> 00:12:59,512
when you could be
capturing them there?

312
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:02,148
Kume, a small lapse
in judgment.

313
00:13:02,148 --> 00:13:05,418
I'll gather the troops
and return immediately, Master.

314
00:13:05,418 --> 00:13:06,786
Never mind.

315
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,855
Huh?

316
00:13:08,855 --> 00:13:10,823
Disappear.

317
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:12,425
♪

318
00:13:12,425 --> 00:13:13,626
Please, give me another chance.

319
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,295
I‐‐I promise, I‐‐I...

320
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,163
(whimpering)

321
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:19,766
Oh, no!

322
00:13:19,766 --> 00:13:22,769
♪

323
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:25,938
Kume!

324
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:30,677
♪

325
00:13:30,677 --> 00:13:31,978
(laughs)

326
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:33,713
♪

327
00:13:33,713 --> 00:13:36,683
Now, Big Blue, prepare.

328
00:13:36,683 --> 00:13:39,319
I can handle this
mission for you myself.

329
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:42,689
Yes, but I'll go too,
just to pass the time.

330
00:13:42,689 --> 00:13:45,591
There's‐‐there's
one more thing, Master.

331
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:46,859
Hmm?

332
00:13:46,859 --> 00:13:49,529
It's about the
slaves who've escaped.

333
00:13:49,529 --> 00:13:51,030
Have they been caught?

334
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,765
Just one so far, but...

335
00:13:52,765 --> 00:13:58,137
♪

336
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:01,307
You run, I'll try
to buy us some time.

337
00:14:01,307 --> 00:14:03,042
(yelling)

338
00:14:03,042 --> 00:14:07,780
♪

339
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:11,551
This should prove to be
interesting entertainment.

340
00:14:11,551 --> 00:14:13,486
(laughs)

341
00:14:13,486 --> 00:14:27,934
♪

342
00:14:27,934 --> 00:14:30,069
I don't see anything yet.

343
00:14:30,069 --> 00:14:31,471
They're there.

344
00:14:31,471 --> 00:14:33,873
The Clays are probably
watching us right now.

345
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:38,678
♪

346
00:14:38,678 --> 00:14:40,947
The unknown here is Pixie.

347
00:14:40,947 --> 00:14:44,484
Wow, she sounds like
a regular cutie pie!

348
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:46,753
Mm‐hmm.

349
00:14:46,753 --> 00:14:48,187
Uh...

350
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:50,523
♪

351
00:14:50,523 --> 00:14:53,025
Expect the worst,
and never, never

352
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:55,395
underestimate your
enemies, my friends.

353
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,296
That's good, solid advice.

354
00:14:57,296 --> 00:15:00,933
Hare, my advice to you
is watch and learn, buddy.

355
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:02,135
Watch and learn.

356
00:15:02,135 --> 00:15:04,670
Strong Tiger, 'chi!

357
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:06,272
That's right.

358
00:15:06,272 --> 00:15:08,541
Don't underestimate.

359
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:09,542
That's right.

360
00:15:09,542 --> 00:15:11,411
Baddies have all
kinds of tricks.

361
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:12,779
Here's the plan.

362
00:15:12,779 --> 00:15:15,248
All we have to do is
hold the Baddies' attention

363
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:17,784
until the humans
have time to escape.

364
00:15:17,784 --> 00:15:20,052
If we get into trouble,
we'll retreat.

365
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:21,521
I never retreat.

366
00:15:21,521 --> 00:15:23,623
Hmm?

367
00:15:23,623 --> 00:15:25,158
Ahh, they're here!

368
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:26,159
Hmm?

369
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:34,133
♪

370
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:39,705
♪

371
00:15:39,705 --> 00:15:41,140
That's Pixie!

372
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:42,408
She looks harmless enough,

373
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:44,677
but she's one of
Moo's top Baddies.

374
00:15:44,677 --> 00:15:47,880
They're the ones everyone
calls the Big Bad Four.

375
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:48,815
Pixie...

376
00:15:48,815 --> 00:15:50,950
♪

377
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:54,854
That Pixie doesn't
look so bad to me.

378
00:15:54,854 --> 00:15:56,722
She looks lonesome.

379
00:15:56,722 --> 00:15:58,758
Hmm?

380
00:15:58,758 --> 00:16:01,694
That big blue fella is
awfully big, isn't he?

381
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:02,795
Yeah.

382
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:04,630
Taking that guy on
will be my pleasure.

383
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:11,504
♪

384
00:16:11,504 --> 00:16:13,940
Show yourselves, fools!

385
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:15,508
Come out now!

386
00:16:15,508 --> 00:16:18,611
We have a friend of yours.

387
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:21,547
(gasping)

388
00:16:21,547 --> 00:16:24,350
Cooperate, and you'll
make it easy for him.

389
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,586
Oh, no, what are we
supposed to do now?

390
00:16:26,586 --> 00:16:27,954
'chi!

391
00:16:27,954 --> 00:16:29,522
Do as he says.

392
00:16:29,522 --> 00:16:32,525
Holly, look, we can't go
out there and face them.

393
00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:35,394
We're easily outnumbered
by about 100 to 1!

394
00:16:35,394 --> 00:16:37,830
But Hare, it's our fault
they've got Mickey,

395
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:40,199
so we can't just
leave him, can we?

396
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:41,234
Nope.

397
00:16:41,234 --> 00:16:42,869
And those are just
the kind of odds

398
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:44,871
that make it a challenge.

399
00:16:44,871 --> 00:16:46,739
What's the problem?

400
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,107
No problem!

401
00:16:48,107 --> 00:16:50,476
Ha, that's our enemy?

402
00:16:50,476 --> 00:16:52,912
♪

403
00:16:52,912 --> 00:16:56,449
A couple of kids
and some scruffy monsters?

404
00:16:56,449 --> 00:16:58,251
Hardly worth our trouble.

405
00:16:58,251 --> 00:17:00,520
What, what did you say?

406
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,255
What's your name, kid?

407
00:17:02,255 --> 00:17:06,125
I'm afraid you just made
your first mistake, big fella!

408
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:09,829
Lesson one: never
underestimate your enemy, pal.

409
00:17:09,829 --> 00:17:11,130
And that's all the free advice

410
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:12,999
you're going to get from me!

411
00:17:12,999 --> 00:17:15,768
Genki's my name,
and we're number one!

412
00:17:15,768 --> 00:17:17,837
You can quote me on that!

413
00:17:17,837 --> 00:17:19,705
Well, well, Genki,

414
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,541
it's nice to meet you.

415
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:23,109
But didn't your mother
ever teach you

416
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:25,378
that little boys shouldn't brag?

417
00:17:25,378 --> 00:17:26,412
What did you say?

418
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:28,881
(growling)

419
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:30,349
Surrender!

420
00:17:30,349 --> 00:17:33,019
Genki, that's not how to win.

421
00:17:33,019 --> 00:17:34,654
Yeah, I guess you're right.

422
00:17:34,654 --> 00:17:36,622
All right, we'll come down,

423
00:17:36,622 --> 00:17:39,692
but you have to promise
to let Mickey go.

424
00:17:39,692 --> 00:17:42,662
I have never
surrendered to anybody.

425
00:17:42,662 --> 00:17:44,196
Tiger!

426
00:17:44,196 --> 00:17:45,898
This isn't your call, Tiger.

427
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,800
The plan is that we give in now,

428
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,703
and then come up
with a plan later, okay?

429
00:17:50,703 --> 00:17:52,605
(growls)

430
00:17:52,605 --> 00:17:54,206
What are you doing?

431
00:17:54,206 --> 00:17:56,042
Humans will be slaves.

432
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:59,679
Master Moo will turn
the monsters into Baddies.

433
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:01,047
(chuckles)

434
00:18:01,047 --> 00:18:03,716
Great planning,
Hare, great planning.

435
00:18:03,716 --> 00:18:05,251
You made a promise.

436
00:18:05,251 --> 00:18:07,553
You said you'd release that man.

437
00:18:07,553 --> 00:18:09,455
So, what about it, Pixie?

438
00:18:09,455 --> 00:18:11,357
I'm so terrible with promises,

439
00:18:11,357 --> 00:18:13,192
I just never ever keep them.

440
00:18:13,192 --> 00:18:14,927
(laughs)

441
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:16,929
A promise is a promise!

442
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,130
'chi!

443
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,199
♪

444
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:21,400
(gasp)

445
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,401
Huh?

446
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:27,406
♪

447
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:29,909
Doesn't a promise
mean anything anymore?

448
00:18:29,909 --> 00:18:31,877
Nobody touches Pixie!

449
00:18:31,877 --> 00:18:33,980
(yells)

450
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,482
♪

451
00:18:36,482 --> 00:18:39,051
What a foolish boy you are.

452
00:18:39,051 --> 00:18:41,287
(exclaiming)

453
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:43,656
I think such bravery
should be rewarded,

454
00:18:43,656 --> 00:18:45,291
don't you, Blue?

455
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,626
Huh?

456
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:47,893
Let him go!

457
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:49,629
♪

458
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:52,531
I just hate to repeat myself.

459
00:18:52,531 --> 00:18:55,234
That's lesson one.

460
00:18:55,234 --> 00:18:56,602
I won't lose!

461
00:18:56,602 --> 00:18:57,837
Mocchi!

462
00:18:57,837 --> 00:18:59,772
(growls)

463
00:18:59,772 --> 00:19:01,040
Don't move!

464
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:04,210
♪

465
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:06,379
You hear me?

466
00:19:06,379 --> 00:19:07,613
'chi!

467
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:09,882
‐Double Pounder, Mocchi!
‐'chi!

468
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:12,985
♪

469
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,287
And now the
Cherry Blossom Blizzard!

470
00:19:15,287 --> 00:19:16,555
Try this!

471
00:19:16,555 --> 00:19:18,691
Cherry Blossom Blizzard, 'chi!

472
00:19:18,691 --> 00:19:20,660
Flame Wall!

473
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,495
♪

474
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:25,431
(yelling)

475
00:19:25,431 --> 00:19:30,169
♪

476
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:32,505
You still haven't won, Pixie!

477
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:35,741
Oh yes, I have.

478
00:19:35,741 --> 00:19:38,644
Lightning!

479
00:19:38,644 --> 00:19:39,945
(lightning zaps)

480
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:42,048
(yelling)

481
00:19:42,048 --> 00:19:43,582
♪

482
00:19:43,582 --> 00:19:46,252
(yelling)

483
00:19:46,252 --> 00:19:48,521
‐Genki!
‐Mocchi!

484
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,089
♪

485
00:19:50,089 --> 00:19:52,491
I win, you lose.

486
00:19:52,491 --> 00:19:55,961
♪

487
00:19:55,961 --> 00:19:57,630
Oh my goodness me.

488
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:00,332
I think they've gone and
they didn't say goodbye.

489
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:02,802
How rude.

490
00:20:02,802 --> 00:20:18,617
♪

491
00:20:18,617 --> 00:20:21,220
Genki, Mocchi?

492
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:25,758
♪

493
00:20:25,758 --> 00:20:27,760
(groaning)

494
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:32,198
♪

495
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:33,199
(yells)

496
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:40,172
♪

497
00:20:40,172 --> 00:20:42,408
There's no way
I'm going to lose.

498
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:47,079
♪

499
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,214
♪ Monsters ♪

500
00:20:48,214 --> 00:20:49,315
♪ Monsters rule ♪

501
00:20:49,315 --> 00:21:14,440
♪

502
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,041
♪ Monsters rule ♪♪

